<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F78FEF648F75669FAF7FD8D" pageId="310" pageNumber="311" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="007606418F78FEF648F75669FAF7FD8D" blockId="310.[151,1436,288,746]" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F78FEF648F75669FEE4FEAE" bold="true" box="[199,321,325,350]" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F78FEF6497C5669FE05FEAD" box="[332,416,325,349]" italics="true" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF649845669FDE8FEAD" box="[436,589,325,349]" captionStart="PLATE 89" captionStartId="308.[151,233,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[278,1352,186,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-37@308.[247,1354,165,1994]" captionTargetPageId="308" captionText="PLATE 89. Female of Pseudodryinus sp. Length 4.5 mm. (from Olmi 1991). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278692/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 89A, B</figureCitation>
): fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64B3F5669FC02FEAD" box="[783,935,325,349]" captionStart="PLATE 89" captionStartId="308.[151,233,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[278,1352,186,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-37@308.[247,1354,165,1994]" captionTargetPageId="308" captionText="PLATE 89. Female of Pseudodryinus sp. Length 4.5 mm. (from Olmi 1991). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278692/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 89A, B</figureCitation>
); palpal formula 3/2, 4/2, 4/3, 5/2, or 5/3; antenna with many long hairs on segments 6–10 (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64AF85645FCFCFE71" box="[712,857,361,385]" captionStart="PLATE 89" captionStartId="308.[151,233,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[278,1352,186,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-37@308.[247,1354,165,1994]" captionTargetPageId="308" captionText="PLATE 89. Female of Pseudodryinus sp. Length 4.5 mm. (from Olmi 1991). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278692/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 89A, B</figureCitation>
); fore wing with three cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal, median and submedian) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64A6C56A1FD56FE55" box="[604,755,397,421]" captionStart="PLATE 89" captionStartId="308.[151,233,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[278,1352,186,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-37@308.[247,1354,165,1994]" captionTargetPageId="308" captionText="PLATE 89. Female of Pseudodryinus sp. Length 4.5 mm. (from Olmi 1991). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278692/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 89A, B</figureCitation>
); protarsus chelate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64BD156A1FBD2FE55" box="[993,1143,397,421]" captionStart="PLATE 89" captionStartId="308.[151,233,2001,2024]" captionTargetBox="[278,1352,186,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-37@308.[247,1354,165,1994]" captionTargetPageId="308" captionText="PLATE 89. Female of Pseudodryinus sp. Length 4.5 mm. (from Olmi 1991). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278692/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 89A, B</figureCitation>
); chela with rudimentary claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF648EC569DFEE8FE39" box="[220,333,433,457]" captionStart="PLATE 90" captionStartId="309.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[208,1392,219,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-116@309.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="309" captionText="PLATE 90. A, E. Mandibles, holotypes. B, C. Maxillary palp (B) and Labial palp (C), holotypes. D, H. Chelae, holotypes. F, G, I,J. Male genitalia, holotypes. A–D. Pseudodryinus beckeri (from Olmi 1991). E, I. P.thai (from Olmi 2008c). F. P. piceus (from Olmi 2011a). G, H.P.sinensis (from Olmi 1993b). J. Neodryinus baishanzuensis (from Xu &amp; He, 1996a). Scale bar 0.57 mm for A, 0.31 mm for B, 0.23 mm for C, I and J, 0.20 mm for D, F and G, 0.34 mm for E, 0.29 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278694/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 90D</figureCitation>
); segment 5 of protarsus less than twice as broad as enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64C71569DFB16FE39" box="[1089,1203,433,457]" captionStart="PLATE 90" captionStartId="309.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[208,1392,219,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-116@309.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="309" captionText="PLATE 90. A, E. Mandibles, holotypes. B, C. Maxillary palp (B) and Labial palp (C), holotypes. D, H. Chelae, holotypes. F, G, I,J. Male genitalia, holotypes. A–D. Pseudodryinus beckeri (from Olmi 1991). E, I. P.thai (from Olmi 2008c). F. P. piceus (from Olmi 2011a). G, H.P.sinensis (from Olmi 1993b). J. Neodryinus baishanzuensis (from Xu &amp; He, 1996a). Scale bar 0.57 mm for A, 0.31 mm for B, 0.23 mm for C, I and J, 0.20 mm for D, F and G, 0.34 mm for E, 0.29 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278694/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 90D</figureCitation>
); enlarged claw with one subapical tooth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF649BD56F9FDA7FE1D" box="[397,514,469,493]" captionStart="PLATE 90" captionStartId="309.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[208,1392,219,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-116@309.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="309" captionText="PLATE 90. A, E. Mandibles, holotypes. B, C. Maxillary palp (B) and Labial palp (C), holotypes. D, H. Chelae, holotypes. F, G, I,J. Male genitalia, holotypes. A–D. Pseudodryinus beckeri (from Olmi 1991). E, I. P.thai (from Olmi 2008c). F. P. piceus (from Olmi 2011a). G, H.P.sinensis (from Olmi 1993b). J. Neodryinus baishanzuensis (from Xu &amp; He, 1996a). Scale bar 0.57 mm for A, 0.31 mm for B, 0.23 mm for C, I and J, 0.20 mm for D, F and G, 0.34 mm for E, 0.29 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278694/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 90D</figureCitation>
)); tibial spurs 1/1/2. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F78FEF64ACB56F9FC91FE1D" box="[763,820,469,493]" italics="true" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64B7956F9FC44FE1D" box="[841,993,469,493]" captionStart="PLATE 91" captionStartId="318.[151,233,1997,2020]" captionTargetBox="[282,1313,185,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-37@318.[243,1345,161,1976]" captionTargetPageId="318" captionText="PLATE 91. Pseudodryinus thai, holotype. Length 2.4 mm (from Olmi 2008c). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278696/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 91A, B</figureCitation>
): fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64C9456F9FA99FE1D" box="[1188,1340,469,493]" captionStart="PLATE 91" captionStartId="318.[151,233,1997,2020]" captionTargetBox="[282,1313,185,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-37@318.[243,1345,161,1976]" captionTargetPageId="318" captionText="PLATE 91. Pseudodryinus thai, holotype. Length 2.4 mm (from Olmi 2008c). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278696/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 91A, B</figureCitation>
); palpal formula 6/3; occipital carina complete; mandible with four irregular teeth (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64BEE56D5FBC9FDE1" box="[990,1132,505,529]" captionStart="PLATE 90" captionStartId="309.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[208,1392,219,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-116@309.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="309" captionText="PLATE 90. A, E. Mandibles, holotypes. B, C. Maxillary palp (B) and Labial palp (C), holotypes. D, H. Chelae, holotypes. F, G, I,J. Male genitalia, holotypes. A–D. Pseudodryinus beckeri (from Olmi 1991). E, I. P.thai (from Olmi 2008c). F. P. piceus (from Olmi 2011a). G, H.P.sinensis (from Olmi 1993b). J. Neodryinus baishanzuensis (from Xu &amp; He, 1996a). Scale bar 0.57 mm for A, 0.31 mm for B, 0.23 mm for C, I and J, 0.20 mm for D, F and G, 0.34 mm for E, 0.29 mm for H." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278694/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 90A, E</figureCitation>
); notauli joint or separated at posterior margin of scutum; if separated, minimum distance between notauli much shorter than greatest breadth of posterior ocelli; fore wing with three cells enclosed by pigmented veins (costal, median and submedian) (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64D54556DFF4DFD8D" captionStart="PLATE 91" captionStartId="318.[151,233,1997,2020]" captionTargetBox="[282,1313,185,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-37@318.[243,1345,161,1976]" captionTargetPageId="318" captionText="PLATE 91. Pseudodryinus thai, holotype. Length 2.4 mm (from Olmi 2008c). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278696/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 91A, B</figureCitation>
); fore wing with metacarpus as long as, or longer than pterostigma (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F78FEF64BD75549FBD2FD8D" box="[999,1143,613,637]" captionStart="PLATE 91" captionStartId="318.[151,233,1997,2020]" captionTargetBox="[282,1313,185,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-37@318.[243,1345,161,1976]" captionTargetPageId="318" captionText="PLATE 91. Pseudodryinus thai, holotype. Length 2.4 mm (from Olmi 2008c). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278696/files/figure.png" pageId="310" pageNumber="311">Plate 91A, B</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
